<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Data Collection Impact</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            text-align: center;
            color: #333;
        }
        p {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }
        label {
            display: block;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
        input[type="text"], input[type="email"] {
            width: calc(100% - 22px);
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        button {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 20px;
            background-color: #007BFF;
            color: #fff;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Understanding the Impact of Data Collection Techniques</h1>
    <p>Below are some of the ways data collection techniques can affect individuals' privacy and security:</p>

    <form action="#" method="post">
        <label for="ssn">Enter Your Social Security Number (SSN) for a Detailed Analysis:</label>
        <input type="text" id="ssn" name="ssn" placeholder="Enter SSN" required>

        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>

    <div>
        <p><strong>1. Surveillance and Monitoring:</strong> Techniques such as mass surveillance and real-time data collection allow continuous monitoring of individuals' activities.</p>
        <p><strong>2. Data Breaches and Security Risks:</strong> Data breaches can expose sensitive information, leading to identity theft and financial fraud.</p>
        <p><strong>3. Psychological Impact:</strong> Constant monitoring can lead to a "chilling effect," where individuals self-censor their thoughts and actions.</p>
        <p><strong>4. Legal and Ethical Concerns:</strong> Mass surveillance often infringes on privacy rights and lacks transparency.</p>
        <p><strong>5. Targeted Advertising and Marketing:</strong> Personalized ads can be intrusive and manipulative.</p>
        <p><strong>6. Identity Theft and Financial Fraud:</strong> Stolen data can result in significant financial losses.</p>
        <p><strong>7. Political and Social Impacts:</strong> Extensive surveillance can erode trust in government and institutions.</p>
        <p><strong>8. Technological Risks:</strong> Weak security measures can leave data vulnerable to hacking and cyber threats.</p>
        <p><strong>9. Health and Well-being:</strong> Medical data can be used for both good and harm, depending on how it is handled.</p>
        <p><strong>10. Corporate Practices:</strong> Data sharing and lack of consent can lead to unintended uses and breaches.</p>
    </div>
</div>

</body>
</html>
```

